And this is when you disappeared. I was expecting you to pop in at night. I was actually interested to see if you were recovering. I got a bit worried the next day, but you had been absent some days before so I was sort of ok. By the second day I was getting really worried – I didn’t realise it at the time, but considering you left while ill, it’s no surprise I was actually afraid something had happened.

After I saw you upload videos, I was relieved. But then I started to wonder why you suddenly decided not to come back to Discord. A lot of things crossed my mind. I thought I had done something wrong but I couldn’t see what. I thought maybe you just got tired of the chat, since it had grown kind of stale. I was ok with that, but I felt _empty_. I did miss it, I got used to you. I was having too much fun.

A lot of things went through my head and I re-read chat. I wasn’t ready to understand it though. That’s when I started to try and see if I could find some pattern that would explain it, but all I kept running into, reading your messages out of context, was stuff that irritated me.

There was one thing I couldn’t get out of my head though, despite otherwise not feeling certain about how to interpret your behavior. I had posted a skyrim video I made and I could see from the analytics that you hadn’t even clicked on it. I thought maybe you just missed it. Then, about 3 days in, you responded to Nicolai’s baby pic. I suspected you were lurking anyway. I couldn’t see any reason why you would have missed it since you hadn’t missed anything else at all. So I took it as you deliberately ignoring it
Usually sniffing sends me into a fit of coughing so I'm glad I'm past that

Whenever I started feeling I was being unfair, I kept thinking back to that, unable to satisfy myself with an explanation. This is where my trust issues come in. I _have_ to believe the worst case, even if I feel it’s not likely. It’s self-defense. That’s why I took it all to mean something it didn’t. Of course you had just missed it and you wanted to disconnect. I was fine with that, even if I didn’t like it, but I _couldn’t_ fit ignoring that video into the pattern.

When you came back, I pinged you with the same video. I was very confused and did that to see how you’d react. When I saw that _again_ you were ignoring it completely I felt _certain_ you were ignoring me on purpose. What felt worse was that it was a video I had made and it felt like you didn’t care to even take a moment to look at it. This got stuck in my head and it’s where my idea that you were only around for attention came from.
I’m still sorry for this. I let it get to my head too much and it _was_ silly. I just couldn’t fit it in and explain it. I will admit I felt a bit hurt, perhaps unfairly. I hope you understand now.
